{"id":"shelah","term":"Shelah","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Petition. (1.) Judah’s third son (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 38:2\">Gen. 38:2</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 38:5\">5</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 38:11\">11</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 38:14\">14</a>).</p>\n<p>(2.) A son of Arphaxad (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 1:18\">1 Chr. 1:18</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 38:2","Genesis 38:5","Genesis 38:11","Genesis 38:14","1 Chronicles 1:18"]}